### Current political subdivisions

The [Virginia Peninsula](/Virginia_Peninsula) subregion, a study in both historical continuity and modern administrative efficiency, currently comprises four distinct [independent cities](/Independent_city): [Hampton](/Hampton,_Virginia), [Newport News](/Newport_News,_Virginia), [Poquoson](/Poquoson,_Virginia), and [Williamsburg](/Williamsburg,_Virginia). These cities, by virtue of [Virginia](/Virginia)'s unique municipal law, operate entirely outside the jurisdiction of any county. In addition to these independent urban centers, the region also includes two counties: [James City County](/James_City_County,_Virginia) and [York County](/York_County,_Virginia). Notably, there are currently no incorporated towns within the geographic bounds of this subregion, a direct consequence of the extensive consolidation trends witnessed in the latter half of the 20th century. Historically, however, the area was populated by a significantly greater number of political subdivisions, many of which are now considered defunct, primarily due to the natural growth of communities and the aforementioned strategic consolidation of local governments, an administrative evolution detailed further in the subsequent section.

